Several papers have used the name
P. pronotalis
( Claver & Fowler, 1993 ; Nobua-Behrmann, Lopez de Casenave, Milesi, & Pavan, 2013;
Nobua Behrmann et al ., 2010
; Pirk & Lopez de Casenave, 2006 ;
Pirk et al ., 2007
;
Pirk et al ., 2004
;
Pirk et al ., 2009
; Pol & Lopez de Casenave, 2004 ; Pol, Lopez de Casenave, Feldhaar, Milesi, & Gadau, 2008), but this name was based on a misidentification, and all of these papers should be referred to
P. mendozanus
(see Johnson, 2015).
